s; May the Force be with you , mate , &apos; &quot; he said . &quot; The cape is an Australian flag . I &apos;ve got beer cans on my belt and blue flames airbrushed onto my helmet and chest piece . I &apos;ve even made a custom light-sabre with a didgeridoo handle . &quot; He has already seen the new Star Wars film Rogue One , once at the red carpet premiere and again at a midnight screening with fans . &quot; It definitely beat all my expectations , &quot; he said , adding that the latest blockbuster is a great tribute to the original trilogy . &quot; Empire Strikes Back was dark and gritty . Rogue One has a lot of those elements too . &quot; Reporting by the BBC &apos;s Greg Dunlop
